snippet.textDisplay:
Hello Again Coke Studio, the concerned Authority and Salim Vai!
Today on the occasion of our National Poet Kazi Nazrul Islam's  birth anniversary, I with due respect and acknowledgement to All of You who performed and played to produce SATI, am presenting here a bangla recitation rendered along with the audio track of SATI, a humble attempt only as a mark of the immense inspiration it brought about in me to pay tribute to our poet of humanity and secularism at this moment of great despair and depression and pay homage to this great piece of musical work's composer and the brilliant Taufique Qureshi as well. 

I made this attempt only to express my gratitude to SATI, whom our poet compared to freedom from fear and repression and all darkness; and also to share the level of ecstatic feeling I had while I tried to perform the poetry in the format of SATI, a great learning for me. I never meant to feature it for any other purpose than salute the magical strength of music-poetry fusion and upholding the power of music as a universal language that can heal us, our heart and the whole world, that can unite us crossing all barriers that keeps humanity apart. 

I am attaching the link here for your kind inspection 
< https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=buVBdvSS81g> 

 Due credit and acknowledgement is given to SATI and all the Artist along with Coke Studio@MTV, India.

snippet.textDisplay:
Hello Again Coke Studio, the concerned Authority and Salim Vai!

I have already shared my thought regarding Sati. This Composition simply got me spell bound and immensely inspired 
to render a Bangla Poetry recitation along with the score in between the vocals and with the percussion 
without distorting any part of its overall essence, Now the poem is by Kazi Nazrul Islam, our National Poet and coming 25 May would be his death Anniversary. We want to pay tribute to our great poet at this darkest hour caused my a global pandemic to share His message of assurance for peace and no fear to humanity,  with this special recital featuring SATI with the recitation, tt would be a different piece of work, only If you kindly give your consent to do so! 

If you want to see a demo, I can send you to your mail ( the ID you have to provide with) to actually present to you what are we going to do! Please respond and bless with your kind permission to pay tribute to a great poet of secularism and humanity Kazi Nazrul Islam.  
Regarding featuring the Score, we will be open to consider and oblige any condition you come up with, prior to that just 
give us a chance to share how it sounds, the poem with SATI 

for any further info: mail: sagarprokash.sen@gmail.com
on facebook find: Sagar Sen (Works at NTV)

snippet.textDisplay:
I have been specially inspired by this great piece of work of the immensely Talented Trio and co musicians. So much so that it got me encouraged to envisage an infusion of a Bangla poetry recitation along with this musical, 
and simulating it in my mind over 50 times got me utterly enthralled! But this is an iconic Coke Studio Copyright Score! And I have utmost respect for that. 
Coke Studio has made a signature that whole world takes a bow !  We music lovers are so grateful, though being a voice over artist I still know how many musicians at home and abroad have been enlightened and enriched by the great legends and icon musicians and artists of the sub-continent been featured here. 
Even such a meagre person like me
has been throbbing in excitement for almost 5 years or more after I had first beheld Sati!! A poem by Kazi Nazrul Islam got lightened into my mind, and after some informal simulative rundown with SATIm, I simply got spell bound! 

I have been mulling through these years since then, asking myself the questions over and over again that  will I ask !(?) 

should I ask The Coke Studio, The Talented Trio including Salim  Vai to just let me share what actually made me so mad about Sati and how madly I want the Bangla poetry recitation to render inside this score without distorting it's core and overall essence of theme, vocal and composition! But at times it made me feel like if I keep it inside my mind, it would be a great miss out! A single score has made such a disruption and caused such a tumult in my heart that I cannot help reciting it, but in my mind only, How can I explain what actually it sounds like. 
If I cannot share with the originators what would be the use! 
I would humbly request The Coke Studio Authority and of course Salim Vai to give me a chance to show a demo, of course with their permission, to give a taste that is overwhelming me for all these years!!
My name is Sagar Sen! I will be hugely grateful to have a node from you! 
Regards
